#library(CausalImpact) # These are the necessary packages for R Shiny: library(shiny) library(bslib) library(bsicons) library(thematic) library(shinyjs) library(shinycssloaders) library(plotly) library(dplyr) library(ggplot2) library(ggstatsplot) library(patchwork) library(RColorBrewer) library(progress) library(data.table) library(memoise) #STAHP COMPLAINING D: options(warn = -1, shiny.reactlog=TRUE) #Put the Base Data here: set.seed(1) x1 <- 100 + arima.sim(model = list(ar = 0.9999), n = 100) y <- 5 * x1 + rnorm(100) y[70:100] <- y[70:100] + 300 data <- cbind(y, x1) ui <- navbarPage( #Similar to thematics, where you just initialize it and it works in the background useShinyjs(), #Puts Title on the Application on the top title = "The Shiniest of Testing âœ¨", #Sets the theme for bslib using the Bootswatch Library: theme = bs_theme( bootswatch = "morph" ), #Creates the sidebar sidebar = sidebar( title = "Controls", fillable = TRUE, accordion_filters <- accordion( id = "the_accordion", accordion_panel( "Intervention Effect", icon = bs_icon("card-checklist"), #Setup with input funcs in Shiny are always input id, then the name in the app #followed by the values sliderInput("inv_mmt", "Intervention Moment", min = 4, max = 96, value = 70, animate = animationOptions( interval = 600, loop = TRUE ) ), div(id = "spinner", "Loading Intervention Moments...", style = "display: none;"), #Switches between the interactive plots through plotly :) input_switch("plotly_switch", "Interactivity through Plotly", value = TRUE) ), div(id = "filters", accordion_panel( title = "Filters", icon = bs_icon("funnel-fill"), selectInput("country_selection", "Select Countries:", choices = NULL, multiple = TRUE) ) ) ) ), # Creates a Tab tabsetPanel( id = "the_tabset", tabPanel( title = "Comparing Periods", value = "cmp_periods", navset_card_underline( id = "the_tabs", nav_panel( title = "Comparing Periods (Base)", value = "tab1", card( full_screen = TRUE, conditionalPanel( full_screen = TRUE, condition = "input.plotly_switch == true", fillPage( plotlyOutput("plot2_plotly", height = "100%") ) ), conditionalPanel( condition = "input.plotly_switch == false", plotOutput("plot2") ) ) ), nav_panel( title = "Comparing Periods (Matrix)", value = "tab3", card( full_screen = TRUE, conditionalPanel( full_screen = TRUE, condition = "input.plotly_switch == true", plotlyOutput("mtx_plotly") ), conditionalPanel( condition = "input.plotly_switch == false", plotOutput("mtxplot") ) ) ), nav_panel( title = "Confidence Bands (Dark Statistical Magic)", value = "tab2", card( #Force HTML Code :) tags$head( tags$style(HTML(" .shiny-image-output img { width: 100%; height: auto; max-height: 70vh; display: block; margin: 0 auto; } .image-container { display: flex; height: 70vh; overflow: hidden; } ")) ), div(class = "image-container", imageOutput("magic_image")) ), ) ), ), tabPanel( title = "Comparing Countries", value = "cmp_countries", card( full_screen = TRUE, plotlyOutput("country_plot") ), ), ), ) server <- function(input, output, session){ #Sets the Plots to the same theme as a bslib theme :D thematic_shiny() showPageSpinner() #Kind of like a list of values to set that can by dynamically allocated v <- reactiveValues( lower_bound = 0, pre.period = 0, post.period = 0, df = NULL, country_choices = NULL, intervention_line = list(), cmp_pds_inv_mmt = NULL, cmp_cts_inv_mmt = NULL ) countries_min_time = 1950 #LOAD FASTER PLS Functions Below :3 #Read Matrices: will_data <- fread("Matrix1.csv") country_data <- reactive ({ #Read the File fread("Data_SC_BSTS.csv") }) memoise_this <- memoise(function(data){ ggbetweenstats( data = data, x = period, y = y, title = "Comparing the Pre and Post Intervention Periods", xlab = "Period", ylab = "Intervention Amounts", ggplot.component = list(theme(text = element_text(size = 14))) ) }) base_plot <- reactive({ memoise_this(data = v$df) }) #Tracks the Intervention Moment and updates the bounds accordingly observeEvent(input$inv_mmt, { v$lower_bound <- input$inv_mmt[1] v$pre.period <- c(1, v$lower_bound) v$post.period <- c(v$lower_bound + 1, 100) v$df <- data.frame( time = 1:nrow(data), y = data[, 1], period = ifelse(1:nrow(data) < v$lower_bound, "1. Pre-intervention", "2. Post-intervention") ) }) observeEvent(input$the_tabset,{ compare_statement <- v$lower_bound < countries_min_time if (input$the_tabset == "cmp_countries" && compare_statement ){ # If the intervention moment is before the minimum time period for the country # save it, so that we can use it later for switching back v$cmp_pds_inv_mmt = input$inv_mmt[1] v$intervention_line <- list( list( type = "line", x0 = countries_min_time, x1 = countries_min_time, y0 = 0, y1 = 1, # The one line of code that makes it fit the entire graph D: yref = "paper", line = list(color = "gray", width = 2, dash = 'dash') ) ) }else if (input$the_tabset == "cmp_periods" && !compare_statement){ v$cmp_cts_inv_mmt = input$inv_mmt[1] v$intervention_line <- list( list( type = "line", x0 = v$cmp_pds_inv_mmt, x1 = v$cmp_pds_inv_mmt, y0 = 0, y1 = 1, # The one line of code that makes it fit the entire graph D: yref = "paper", line = list(color = "gray", width = 2, dash = 'dash') ) ) } else{ v$intervention_line <- list( list( type = "line", x0 = v$lower_bound, x1 = v$lower_bound, y0 = 0, y1 = 1, # The one line of code that makes it fit the entire graph D: yref = "paper", line = list(color = "gray", width = 2, dash = 'dash') ) ) } }) #Looks complicated, just isn't observeEvent({ input$the_tabs input$the_tabset},{ if (input$the_tabs == "tab1"){ updateSliderInput(session, "inv_mmt", min = 4, max = 96, value = v$cmp_pds_inv_mmt) shinyjs::show("plotly_switch") } else { updateSliderInput(session, "inv_mmt", min = 51, max = 91, value = v$cmp_pds_inv_mmt) } #Gotta hide the switch for the "dark magics" if (input$the_tabs == "tab2"){ shinyjs::hide("plotly_switch") } if (input$the_tabs == "tab3"){ shinyjs::show("plotly_switch") } #Makes sure that the slider input is consistent with what is available for #each intervention moment in each tab if (input$the_tabset == "cmp_countries"){ if (is.null(v$cmp_cts_inv_mmt)){ v$cmp_cts_inv_mmt <- 1990 } updateSliderInput(session, "inv_mmt", min = countries_min_time, max = 2023, value = v$cmp_cts_inv_mmt) shinyjs::hide("plotly_switch") shinyjs::show("filters") } if (input$the_tabset == "cmp_periods"){ shinyjs::hide("filters") } }) observe({ data <- country_data() updateSelectInput(session, "country_selection", choices = unique(data$country), selected = "Venezuela (Bolivarian Republic of)") if (is.null(input$inv_mmt)) return() if (input$inv_mmt == isolate(input$inv_mmt)){ shinyjs::hide("spinner") } else { shinyjs::show("spinner") } }) # output$plot <- renderPlot({ # #Scaling the Bounds of the Intervention Effect # impact <- CausalImpact(data,v$pre.period, v$post.period) # the_plot <- plot(impact, "pointwise") + # geom_hline(yintercept = 10, # col = 'red') + # plot(impact, c("original", "cumulative")) # # plot(the_plot) # # # }) output$plot2_plotly <- renderPlotly({ hidePageSpinner() p <- base_plot() # ggplotly(p) %>% # style( # hovertemplate = paste( # "Time: %{customdata[0]}
", # "Period: %{customdata[1]}
", # "Intervention Amount: %{y}" # ), # text = ~paste("Time:", v$df$time, "
Period:", v$df$period, "
Intervention Amount:", v$df$y), # customdata = cbind(v$df$time, v$df$period) # ) }) output$plot2 <- renderPlot ({ base_plot() }) output$magic_image <- renderImage({ # Formatting the string so that it corresponds to the lower_bound number: imagename <- sprintf("www/Intervention%d.png", v$lower_bound) # Display the image list(src = imagename, contentType = 'image/png', alt = "Causal Impact Graph", height = "auto", width = "100%") }, deleteFile = FALSE) output$mtxplot <- renderPlot({ inv_adj_amt = v$lower_bound - 50 yval = paste0("V", inv_adj_amt) #TODO: Fill this out soon... actual_data <- data.frame(time = 1:nrow(data), y = data[,1]) p <- ggplot() + geom_line(data = actual_data, aes(x = time, y = y), color = 'black', size = 1, linetype = "solid", name = "Actual Data") + geom_line(data = will_data, aes_string(x = "1:nrow(will_data)", y = yval), color = 'blue', size = 1, linetype = "dashed", name = "Predicted Data") + geom_vline(xintercept = v$lower_bound, color = "gray", linetype = "dashed", size = 1) + labs(title = 'Comparing the Pre and Post Intervention Periods', x = 'Time Period', y = 'Intervention Moments') + theme_minimal() + theme(plot.background = element_rect(fill = "white"), legend.position = "bottom") plot(p) }) output$mtx_plotly <- renderPlotly({ #Adjust the intervention amount based on the columns of the matrix inv_adj_amt <- v$lower_bound - 50 #Correspond it to the column of the matrix yval = paste0("V", inv_adj_amt) actual_data <- data.frame(time = 1:nrow(data), y = data[,1]) fig <- plot_ly(x = actual_data$time, y = actual_data$y, type = 'scatter', mode = 'lines', name = "Actual Data", line = list(color = 'rgb(0,0,0)'))%>% layout(title = list(text = "Comparing the Pre and Post Intervention Periods", xanchor = "center", yanchor = "top"), autosize = TRUE, plot_bgcolor='#e5ecf6', xaxis = list( title = 'Time Period'), yaxis = list( title = 'Intervention Moments'), showlegend = TRUE, #Create a Vertical Line to indicate the intervention moment: shapes = v$intervention_line ) #Create a "Layer" to show the Predicted Data extrapolated from the matrix :) fig <- fig %>% add_trace(y = will_data[[yval]], name = 'Predicted Data', line = list(color = 'rgb(51,171,249)', dash = 'dash') ) }) filtered_data <- reactive({ df <- country_data() selected_countries <- input$country_selection df <- df %>% filter (country %in% selected_countries) return(df) }) output$country_plot <- renderPlotly({ req(filtered_data()) req(input$country_selection) data <- filtered_data() fig <- plot_ly(type = 'scatter', mode = 'lines') selected_countries <- input$country_selection #Generate a color palette based on the number of countries selected #Maximum is there because RColorBrewer prefers having at least 3 colors <- RColorBrewer::brewer.pal(max(2 * length(selected_countries), 3), "Set1") for (i in seq_along(selected_countries)){ country_data <- data %>% filter(country == selected_countries[i]) #Add the Actual Data into the plot: fig <- fig %>% add_trace(data = country_data, x = ~year, y = ~y1, name = selected_countries[i], line = list(color = colors[i]), inherit = TRUE) #Add the Expected Data into the plot: expected_name <- paste0("Expected Data of ", selected_countries[i]) fig <- fig %>% add_trace(data = country_data, x = ~year, y = ~y2, name = expected_name, line = list(color = colors[2*i+1], dash = 'dash'), inherit = TRUE) } fig <- fig %>% layout(title = list(text = "GDP Per Capita and their Expected GDPs", xanchor = "center", yanchor = "top"), autosize = TRUE, plot_bgcolor='#e5ecf6', xaxis = list( title = 'Time Period'), yaxis = list( title = 'GDP per Capita'), showlegend = TRUE, #Create a Vertical Line to indicate the intervention moment: shapes = v$intervention_line ) }) # Ends the app when the user gets out of the shiny app in the tab # DO NOT PUSH this into GIT and HOST IT (LOCAL DEV ONLY) session$onSessionEnded(stopApp) } shinyApp(ui,server)
